{"id": 1225, "date": "1988-09-01T11:00:24", "date_gmt": "1988-09-01T18:00:24", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=1225"}, "modified": "2026-02-24T18:08:30", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-25T02:08:30", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-patti-scialfa-and-bruce-springsteen-rose", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/09/01/meeting-across-the-river-patti-scialfa-and-bruce-springsteen-rose/", "title": {"rendered": "Rose"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Spotlight on Patti Scialfa today:</p>\n<p>Although Patti released &#8220;Rose&#8221; on her 2004 album\u00a0<em>23rd Street Lullaby</em>, well-connected Bruce fans were already familiar with the song from the legendary Asbury Park all-start holiday concerts that Bruce hosted in 2000. Patti performed the song with Bruce backing her at both holiday shows that year.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-1225-3\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Bruce-Springsteen-10-Rose-online-audio-converter.com_.mp3?_=3\" /><a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Bruce-Springsteen-10-Rose-online-audio-converter.com_.mp3\">http://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Bruce-Springsteen-10-Rose-online-audio-converter.com_.mp3</a></audio>\n<p>But the song dates much farther back than that.</p>\n<p>How far back, I don&#8217;t know. But we do know that Patti performed it more than twenty years prior to those holiday shows, at a <em>Sounds of Asbury Park</em> concert at the Paramount Theater on August 30, 1980&#8211;and amazingly, we have a wonderful video recording of that performance:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/sFVSenqJ9os?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Patti has often said that she based this song on a real person, a woman she used to waitress with when she first moved to New York City. If Rose was pushing 50 in 1980, she&#8217;s pushing 90 today. Let&#8217;s hope she got to appreciate being immortalized in song.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the official studio track, with Bruce on guitar and keyboards:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NdnIETu9IaE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Rose</strong><br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> December 17, 2000 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> December 18, 2000 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 March 21, 2018</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Spotlight on Patti today, as Bruce backs her on one of her earliest songs. Great archive footage from 1980 on this one!</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 68001, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_